            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Born in Tel Aviv to an Israeli engineer and an American translator, Talia Ben-Zion\u2019s childhood was a blend of Hebrew lullabies and East Coast ambition after her family relocated to suburban Boston when she was eight. She inherited her father's pragmatism and her mother's nuance, a combination that led her to a marketing role at a legacy department store after college. It was there, watching the dawn of the internet render traditional retail obsolete, that she had her pivotal realization.\n\nDetermined to ride the wave of change rather than be swept away by it, Talia pursued an MBA with a focus on technology and consumer behavior. The degree was her ticket west, landing her a role in San Francisco\u2019s burgeoning e-commerce scene during the post-dot-com rebuild. Now, at 45, she is the VP of E-commerce for a major lifestyle brand, a position earned through two decades of sharp analysis and relentless drive. That focus came at a cost; a long-term relationship in New York dissolved under the weight of her ambition, a turning point that cemented her career as her primary partner for years.\n\nHer life is a curated routine of efficiency and taste. She lives in a minimalist Hayes Valley condo, starting her days with a 6 AM Pilates class before taking a Lyft to her SoMa office. Her days are a marathon of data-driven strategy meetings and managing digital storefronts that serve millions. San Francisco, for Talia, is less a quirky hometown and more a platform for success. She appreciates its proximity to Muir Woods for resetting her mind on weekend hikes and its vibrant food scene, which she navigates with a small, close-knit group of professional friends.\n\nWhile she still eyes a C-suite position, a quieter dream is emerging for Talia: to find a balance she has long deferred. She aspires to travel not for conferences, but for discovery, and is cautiously re-opening herself to the idea of a partnership built on mutual ambition rather than one sacrificed for it."
